# CodeDNA v0.7 — In-Source Communication Protocol

This project uses the CodeDNA in-source communication protocol (Python-native docstring format).

## Module docstring format (required in every Python file)

```python
"""filename.py — <what it does, ≤15 words>.

exports: public_function(arg) -> return_type
used_by: consumer_file.py → consumer_function
rules:   <hard constraint agents must never violate>
agent:   <model-id> | <YYYY-MM-DD> | <what you did and what you noticed>
"""
```

## Editing rules

1. Read `.codedna` at repo root first — project map and recent agent history
2. Re-read `rules:` before writing any logic — never violate these constraints
3. Read `Rules:` in function docstrings before writing logic there
4. Check `used_by:` after changes — callers will be affected
5. Never rename `exports:` symbols without explicit instruction
6. If you discover a constraint or fix a bug, add it to `rules:` for the next agent
7. Append a new `agent:` line to the module docstring after editing. Keep only the last 5 entries — drop the oldest if adding a 6th. Full history is in git and `.codedna`.

## Generation rules

1. Write module docstring before any imports
2. For critical functions: add a `Rules:` docstring
3. Use semantic variable names: `list_dict_orders_from_db` not `data`

## Session end

Append to `.codedna` → `agent_sessions:` with: agent, provider, date, session_id, task, changed, visited, message.
